## Important NOTE!
It's update for initial PR (#27915), which is closed due to inactivity (I had some work and not enough time for making this update).

There was some discussion about of this changes, so I'll add the most important part of it here:

> But even skipping case, where isomorphic-fetch can't be replaced by `node-fetch`, `@types/isomorhpic-fetch` is separate package and has it's own use case.
In case of browser or isomorphic application, you don't need this `.d.ts`, because `dom.lib.d.ts` already included and it provides fetch out of the box. So `@types/isomorhpic-fetch` used ONLY for node.js when `dom` isn't included.
For whatever reason somebody decided to use fetch polyfill instead of importing fetch from its package, `@types/isomorphic-fetch` should work properly and reflect correct fetch API.
Also, don't forget that `node-fetch` (which is base for `isomorphic-fetch`) differs from browser fetch (mostly in using node.js streams) and this also should be reflected.

So, my main point is that this typings is n **NEVER** used together with `dom.lib.d.ts` so they **SHOULDN'T** rely on it.
